## Extended `BuildRunnerOptions`

The existing options interface may need additional fields:

```typescript
export interface BuildRunnerOptions {
  db: Database;
  projectId: string;
  deploymentId: string;  // NEW: specific deployment record to update
  commitSha: string;
  branch: string;
  cloneUrl: string;       // e.g., https://github.com/owner/repo.git
  installationId: number; // GitHub App installation ID (for token)
  onLog?: (line: string) => void;  // NEW: callback for real-time log streaming (Step 5)
}
```

The `deploymentId` is needed to update the specific deployment record (rather than matching on projectId + commitSha, which could be ambiguous for rollbacks). The `onLog` callback enables Step 5's real-time log streaming.

