## Verification

- [ ] `BuildRunner.run()` successfully clones a public repo (using installation token)
- [ ] The clone is shallow (`--depth 1`) and single-branch
- [ ] `deploy.yaml` is read and parsed if present in the repo root
- [ ] Framework auto-detection is used as fallback when no `deploy.yaml` exists
- [ ] Package manager is detected from the lockfile
- [ ] Dependency cache is restored from S3 when available
- [ ] Dependencies are installed with the correct package manager command
- [ ] The build command runs to completion
- [ ] A Dockerfile is generated for Next.js and static projects
- [ ] User-provided Dockerfiles are used as-is for `framework: "dockerfile"`
- [ ] A Docker image is built and tagged as `{projectSlug}:{commitSha}`
- [ ] Old images are pruned (keeping 10 per project)
- [ ] Build cache is saved to S3 after successful build
- [ ] The deployment record is updated to `status: "deploying"` with `imageTag` and `buildDurationMs`
- [ ] The deployment record is updated to `status: "failed"` with `errorMessage` on failure
- [ ] The build directory is cleaned up after build (success or failure)
- [ ] Build timeout (15 min) kills the build and marks it as FAILED
- [ ] `pnpm typecheck` passes with no errors
